      "questionText": "<p>Consider the following sequence of reactions:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m6w56qt5/d2d5a49f-de5b-472f-85c8-f4356f33cf31/11dd1290-e614-11ef-a9f5-1d03056aff74/file-jaoe38c1m6w56qt6.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m6w56qt5/d2d5a49f-de5b-472f-85c8-f4356f33cf31/11dd1290-e614-11ef-a9f5-1d03056aff74/file-jaoe38c1m6w56qt6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 28th January Morning Shift Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 25 English\"></p>\n<p>11.25 mg of chlorobenzene will produce ___________$\\times 10^{-1} \\mathrm{mg}$ of product B.</p> \n<p>(Consider the reactions result in complete conversion.)</p>\n<p>[Given molar mass of $\\mathrm{C}, \\mathrm{H}, \\mathrm{O}, \\mathrm{N}$ and Cl as $12,1,16,14$ and $35.5 \\mathrm{~g} \\mathrm{~mol}^{-1}$ respectively]</p>",
